summaries.short: After the council learns that Governor Daan is dead and Kurt has escaped, Kalia holds Maran responsible.
summaries.full: After the council learns that Governor Daan is dead and Kurt has escaped, Kalia holds Maran responsible, leaving him embittered and vulnerable to Adnan’s influence. When Moresby vanishes, Kalia discovers what he’d been looking for. Armed with knowledge of the ledgers, Kalia plans to parlay with De Witt once again.

summaries.short: While Kalia is held captive, Adnan takes control of Grisse; Ryuichi faces off with an old acquaintance.
summaries.full: While Kalia is held captive, Adnan takes control of Grisse. As the Dutch gloat, Ryuichi sneaks into their camp and finds himself facing off with an old acquaintance. In Kalia’s absence, Chi remains loyal and stands her ground against Adnan.

summaries.short: A bizarre stranger creates a stir and finds himself imprisoned after sneaking into Grisse.
summaries.full: A bizarre stranger creates a stir and finds himself imprisoned after sneaking into Grisse. Meanwhile, loyalties are redrawn when Sultan Adnan and his royal guards arrive in town, threatening Kalia’s authority. As the Dutch continue to lay siege to Grisse, hidden agendas begin to reveal themselves.

summaries.short: Kalia, along with Chi’s gang, is imprisoned after refusing to surrender; later, Kalia and Adnan duel for rightful leadership of Grisse.
summaries.full: Kalia, along with Chi’s gang, is imprisoned after refusing to surrender to Adnan. When the townspeople gather to demand Kalia’s release, Lena orders the royal guards to beat them into submission, causing a horrified Maran to question his new leaders. Later, Kalia and Adnan duel for rightful leadership of Grisse.

summaries.full: When the Dutch army threatens to attack Grisse, the new town council must decide whether to surrender or fight. All seems hopeless until Kalia discovers a secret weapon and leverages it against De Witt, the feared Dutch major general.

summaries.full: Season One Finale. The council devises a plan to trap De Witt’s army. Kalia brokers a deal with De Witt’s adjutant, Dirk, while Kurt reclaims an old debt. The Dutch make their final descent, as the fate of Grisse hangs in the balance.

summaries.short: When the town erupts into chaos, the people of Grisse must elect a leader to unite and protect them.
summaries.full: When the town erupts into chaos following the rebellion, the people of Grisse must elect a leader to unite and protect them. But, weary of the imminent Dutch return, the townspeople begin to flee, and Kalia is forced to make a difficult decision.
